cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper deals with the problem of building a password cracking server that preserves the privacy of the queries made to the server. This problem falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of cloud-computing services and storage of tables, which could be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and databases (cs.DB). The use of Private Information Retrieval (PIR) protocols could be categorized under cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the technical details and implementation of the method could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
